title: For Sale:  1964 Chinese SKS Type 56 Plant 26 UNFIRED!
postcontent: This is a 1964 Chinese Norinco Type 56 SKS manufactured at Factory 26 which is where Chinese SKS production first occured. All matching numbers. The receiver has the Factory 26 logo, Chinese characters for Type 56, and the S#. This factory was responsible for producing the military SKS production, not commercial. This SKS was manufactured in 1964 and has the original and correct blade bayonet. The Chinese went to the spike bayonet in 1965. This rifle is in excellent condition and may be unfired. The last 5 digits of the serial number appear on the carrier, bolt, trigger guard, and stock. They were military production, used by the Chinese military.  The rifle has the original cleaning kit in the butt, original blade bayonet, Chinese sling, and 20 round magazine.  This is the new rifle a soldier would be issued.   If you are searching for a quality SKS with lots of life left, this is the one.  Text REDACTED
